	"img": "icons/commodities/flowers/strawberry-single-white.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Eyebright is a hemiparasitic plant, having chlorophyll of its own while also attaching to the roots of a host plant. It has oval, sharply toothed leaves, and white, violet-like flowers that have purple veins and yellow centers. It contains chemicals that might reduce inflammation and kill bacteria.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Effect.</strong></em> When ingested as a tea, a dose of eyebright enables you to immediately repeat the saving throw you made against the [[/condition id=blinded]] condition. The tea can be prepared in advance, and consuming a dose of eyebright tea follows all the rules for drinking a potion. If the new saving throw is failed, a second dose would provide a second new save, but if ingested in the same 24-hour period you must also make a successful DC 13 Constitution saving throw or gain a short-term mental stress effect for 24 hours.</p>",
